This paper discusses bitmap indexes commonly used in databases and search engines, which falls under the category of data management (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new compressed bitmap format and compares it to existing techniques, which involves data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also evaluates the performance of the different techniques, which could fall under the categories of computer networks and communications (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
